ont></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bogarthamule>Bogarthamule</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>VoF</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(12/20/02 2:34:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=410.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AoW and the Guild Rep forum</span><hr size=1> Karadin, I understand what you say, but you MUST see the difference in fairness with using the &quot;Only kill on your Statue turn&quot; rule NOW than when you guys did AoW.  When you, SoT, and TL started trying AoW, you 3 along with BotS were the only guilds on the Statue rotation.  You could make an attempt every 20 days, but probably faster with patches.<br>
<br>
Now, there are 9 active guilds on the Statue rotation, and that number will increase steadily in the future.  So guilds wanting to try now would probably have to wait at least 30-35 days in between attempts (and that's accounting for some patches speading it up).  Guilds coming on the Statue rotation now would probably have to wait as long as 50 days in between attempts by the time they are AoWable.<br>
<br>
We're bringing up points of what BotS, TL, NB, SoT have done in the past.  This is obviously done to provide the arguement of &quot;It worked for us so it should for you.&quot;  All things being equal, it would be fair to keep those rules.  Things are NOT equal though, and rules should be modified.  Just because a rule worked for guilds once, doesn't mean that rule shouldn't evolve with changing circumstances.  The past AoW rule is outdated, and should therefore be revised...it's as simple as that. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=karadin>Karadin</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NB-GM<BR>
And supermodel</span><br>  Posts: 289<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(12/20/02 3:15:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=410.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   AOW</span><hr size=1> I do understand, and am ok with changing the rules so that guilds don't have to wait till they're Statue rotation.  However, I fail to see the fairness where guilds that have not proven themselves capable of being on rotation get MORE chances at a mob that guilds that have proven themselves.  Killing every other AoW or every AoW till you get it right is downright unfair.  And citing LoM or FK or whoever as having done this already is by no means a proof of fairness.  It brings to mind when I was young and my sister would demand to get to stay up till my bedtime, just because I did.  Simply, two wrongs don't make a right, and LoM committing what is in my opinion, an infraction, doesn't mean that VoF gets to.  I just don't keep tabs on other guilds enough to track what they are up to on any given night.<br>
<br>
Rotations are about sharing content between those who can kill, making sure said mobs die, and maximizing the loot brought onto the server on a weekly basis.  Guilds that prove themselves capable get to be on said rotations - how is it fair that guilds NOT on a rotation can threaten to risk every or every other spawn of a mob they aren't on rotation for.  Guilds on rotation should see the mob on rotation at least as often as those attempting to get on, especially for mobs that are &quot;wasted&quot; when you try them.  Even on a mob that isn't wasted would wear my patience thin if night after night Guild ABC was keeping us from him by trying him time and again.  Escalate that to a mob that poofs when you fail, and it becomes even more heinous.<br>
<br>
Emp is the same way, so please don't complain how it's just the Big Three trying to keep the up and coming guilds down.  We are about to try Emp.  BotS got to do Emp to their heart's content until they got him right, that is the benefit of being first.  We have more information about the fight than they did, that is the advantage of coming along later.  I shouldn't be allowed to night after night keep popping and wasting chances for Tindi or BotS to get loot off Emp &quot;just cause we think we got it licked this time&quot;.  (Emp isn't wasted per se, but he can only be spawned once every so many hours - thus keeping rotation guilds from trying mobs they have proven they can kill).<br>
<br>
To summarize, I am ok with a change of the Statue rule, but you cannot deny the linkage of the Idol to Statue making any &quot;race&quot; a farce.  However, I will not watch VoF or any guild pop and risk multiple AoWs to NB's one per cycle.   We've proved ourselves, and once you do (not if), you will see things quite a bit differently than you do now.  You will appreciate not having to watch Guild ABC pop and waste 4-5 AoWs in 5-10 spawns so that you get to wait for them to finally kill it before you get to loot him again. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#00FFFF>- </font><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency>The Rathe Travel Agency Board</a><font color=#00FFFF> - </font><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50>General</a> <font color=#00FFFF> - </font><a href="http://www.jakefitch.com/rta/Calendar.asp">The Rathe Calendar</a><font color=#00FFFF> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.229<br>Copyright ©1999-2003 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

